      <title>NASA&apos;s New Horizons Beams Back Pluto Map; Features Resemble &apos;Whale&apos; And &apos;Donut&apos;</title>
      <description>NASA&amp;rsquo;s New Horizon&amp;rsquo;s spacecraft has beamed back a new map of Pluto&amp;rsquo;s light and dark surface features including pixelated areas that the mission science team says resemble the shapes of a &amp;ldquo;whale&amp;rdquo; and a &amp;ldquo;donut.&amp;rdquo; Planetary scientists are quick to point out that although oddly-shaped, they are completely natural and most likely due to the dwarf planet&amp;rsquo;s unique dark topography and brightly-colored condensing surface frosts.</description>
